The mixed exercises provide comprehensive practice across all skills from the lesson:

* Writing equations in slope-intercept form from given slope and [ y ]-intercept, including fractional slopes.
* Graphing lines from slope and [ y ]-intercept.
* Graphing functions given in standard form.
* Writing equations from graphed lines (requires interpreting graphs).
* Multi-part real-world problems involving movies, factory heating, savings accounts, and charity walks, requiring students to write equations, graph, and interpret results.
* Analyzing a specific linear function over a restricted domain, completing a table, and identifying maximum and minimum values.
